                  <msItem>
                     <p> 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Henry</forename> de
                        <surname>Stainegrive</surname>
                        </persName> pledges himself that the 4 acres
                  of land which <persName>
                           <forename>Ralph</forename>, son of <persName>
                              <forename>Richard</forename> ad
                        <surname>Wel</surname> his man</persName>
                        </persName>, demised to the <orgName key="org_103012">prior and convent
                  of Drax</orgName> for eight years, from the feast of St. Martin next after the election of 
                  master Philip as bishop of Durham, at 8s. rent, shall be enjoyed by 
                  them for that time, for the first two years in the middle of his croft, and for the next 
                  six in the cultivated land nearest to the house of Walkelin.
                     (<origDate when="1197">1197</origDate>.)
                     . </p>
